caption: Been trying to find good Döner all over the city. Found some decent places. Tava definitely delivers the goods. I'm happy to have just moved into the neighborhood. I'll come back and have more chicken gyros as much as I can. The staff is mad friendly and the food is very tasty. I've had turkish food in my life in the past 10 years, and this place is not only authentic but genuine and delicious.
We loved the food, especially there fries were so amazing, they put some special spice on top of fries which increased the taste of fries by double or even triple.
I love this Restaurant. The food is delicious and the service is amazing!
the chicken shish kabob was very good.I don’t recommend the chicken gyro

Been searching for a place that does Kahvalti (Turkish Breakfast). Finally found this one. The breakfast platter is decent. The tea is excellent! The Yogurtlu Lamb Gyro was also good. Service was brilliant- the staff are quite friendly, helpful and accommodating.
Decided to try the Lunch Special today and what a surprise, great portions and extremely flavorful. Well worth the $14.

First and foremost. Food is so good! I've been twice already and it has been on point. The adana wrap is my favorite. The first time I went there was a lady working. She was warm, friendly, and helpful.  The second time was a huge service disappointment. It was a weekday morning (They open at 11) so I went for a stroll until they opened. I stopped by at 11:10am and the sign on the door still said closed, but I saw a guy in there, so I cracked the door and asked if they were open. From a distance he said "I don't think so" and kept browsing his phone. (I thought he was double checking or something). I literally stood there with the door cracked, waiting for him to let me know. Nothing. Didn't make eye contact, didn't acknowledge me. Then he went and started setting up his laptop on a table and making himself coffee. So I asked again. And he said they are open. I had to ask him myself if I could order something, he took my order, and went back to his phone.  Then he comes with the tab slip. I reach out my hand for it and instead, he puts it on the counter right in front of my hand. I hand him my card. And AGAIN, he puts my card and the slip on the counter. I should have just left, to be honest. I felt really unwelcomed.  Then he went back to his phone and kept hanging out by the back doorway to the kitchen as I waited for 30 mins. I had to ask him myself when the food would be read. And then again because didn't remember to check on it/grab it when it was time.  You can see in the pics the sign still not being turned to open. The restaurant empty and the guy not in sight + my signed slip and pen still just laying there on the counter.  This experience alone has deterred me from going back so far.
OBSESSED! In love with the mashed potato, shrimp and lahmacun! Can’t wait to try everything on the menu! I order every week, can’t get enough of it! Good quality and delicious!

Everything in this restaurant is perfect - delicious truly Truskish food, wonderful warm service, tasteful ambiance, extremely reasonable prices, generous portions... I can go on forever about this place. It's just perfect.  I'm half-Turkish so I spent a lot of time in Turkey and grew up with Turkish food. Tava felt like eating in my family's kitchen... We had Lahmacun, lentil soup, and the selection of cold appetizers. Everything was very fresh, flavorful, and true to tradition. I almost cried during this meal because of all the memories and emotions it evoked. On top of that, they make a bomb Turkish coffee, which is extremely hard to come by in NYC (and it was on the house, thanks for being so generous 🙏🏼)  The staff was extremely welcoming and accomodating. We even met Ahmed (the owner?) who told us about the restaurant and let me practice my weak Turkish...  All in all, this was one of the best meals I've had in a long time. And I would easily say that this is one of the best Turkish / Mediterranean restaurants outside Turkey that I've been to.  Thank you for making this experience magical. I'm beyond happy to have found this spot and we will be coming back very often.

We stumbled upon this place on Yelp while trying to look for a place to eat at Park Slope. The walk from the subway station at 7th Ave was totally worth it. The bread offered on the table is just what bread should be - warm, soft, and full of flavor. The yogurtlu adana kebab was a surprise and a pleasant one to boot. The meat and croutons smothered with a tart and sweet tomato and yogurt mixture all complemented each other. My dining companions also thoroughly enjoyed their chicken adana and pides. The hot sauce was a lovely surprise. Not terribly hot, with a good depth of tomatoey-tarty flavor. The service put our experience over the top. All of the servers were attentive when needed and left us alone at other times. Definitely a place to stop by for some delicious and fresh healthy-ish food!

We stumbled upon this place as we were visiting Brooklyn and wanted to eat Turkish. Were really surprised by the quality of their food - I ordered lamb shish, and they had probably the most tender cubes of lamb I had in my life... I guess the meat was excellent quality and had marinated for a long time. We also tried some of their starters and pide, and had the impression that everything they serve here is truly homemade: falafels were cooked to perfection and prepared fresh with their own recipe, same with the hummus (which I found a bit too mild in taste, but that could be my personal preference). Great service as well. Will definitely come back again.
Highly recommend!

This is the best Turkish food I ever eaten in New York.. For Turkish people, its really hard to find real Turkish food in the city..Turkish restaurants basicly just cooks a copy of the food that we eat in Turkey..But Tava apparently made us surprized.. Tava’s Lahmacun is the best one in the city, no doubt..its made as thin as a paper..and so crunchy.. The liver is so soft and tasty.. Spicy ezme and yogurt dip my favorite colds.. Lamb adana, chicken and lamb kebabs are also one of the best you can ever find in NY.. The staff is so friendly..They are making sure the customers leave the restaurant so pleasant..

I cannot wait to go back TBH.
